<hr color="#660066" size="20"><a id="fus_17" name=""><br>
<div align="center">
<center>
<table border="0" cellpadding="0" cellspacing="0" style="border-collapse: collapse" width="80%">
<tr>
<td width="100%">
<font size="2" color="#FFFFFF">Ornate Orb of Mastery and pet focus augmentations</font><font size="2"> - 11-12-2003 04:35</font><br><br></td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td width="100%"><font size="2">If you are the owner of an Ornate Orb of Mastery, please do not place an augmentation on it with the purpose of focusing your epic pet. The Ornate Orb must be equipped in the primary hand to focus the pet, but the Orb of Mastery must also be equipped in the primary hand to summon the pet. Obviously you can&#39;t have two items in the same hand, so if you place such an augment (specifically the Diamond Prism of Companionship) on you Ornate Orb, you will not be able to focus your epic pet. <br><br>If you currently have the Diamond Prism of Companionship bonded to your Ornate Orb of Mastery, you may petition your GM and they will reimburse the item for you. <br><br>There&#39;s some history behind this problem, but the message above is the important thing. <br><br>When the Diamond Prism was introduced, it was not intended to focus the epic pet, and some Mages placed them on their Ornate Orb of Mastery. Recently we changed the Prism to focus Mage epic pets, and thus this problem occurred. <br><br>- Alan</font><br><br></td>
</tr>
